00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:29.679
We find that even in battle,

00:02:29.679 --> 00:02:33.339
that the enemy sometimes will try to distract

00:02:33.339 --> 00:02:35.940
through some type of decoy and what have you

00:02:35.940 --> 00:02:39.660
in order to get the attention of the opposing army

00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:43.080
to be distracted while something's taking place over here.

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:45.759
And we see even in the spiritual realm

00:02:45.759 --> 00:02:47.919
that there are many distractions.

00:02:47.919 --> 00:02:50.360
And a good soldier, he avoids distraction.

00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:52.639
We said a good soldier from verse number four,

00:02:52.639 --> 00:02:55.339
that he seeks to please his master.

00:02:55.339 --> 00:02:57.520
Oh, I hope that your goal and your desire,

00:02:57.520 --> 00:02:59.080
we think about the Christian life

00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:01.279
and understanding that if you're saved this morning,

00:03:01.279 --> 00:03:03.600
that you'll stand before the Lord Jesus Christ

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:06.000
at the judgment seat of Christ, the bema.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.520
And I hope as we see often in the New Testament

00:03:08.520 --> 00:03:10.240
and the gospel accounts that we'll hear,

00:03:10.240 --> 00:03:13.240
well done, thou good and faithful servant,

00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:15.919
that we live our lives in such a way

00:03:15.919 --> 00:03:18.080
that we desire to please the Lord.

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:20.679
