00:08:04.380 --> 00:08:07.299
Consider with me a few thoughts this morning

00:08:07.299 --> 00:08:10.119
with regard to the exhortation to work hard.

00:08:10.119 --> 00:08:12.760
There are many people that erroneously have the idea

00:08:12.760 --> 00:08:15.779
that work was a result of the fall.

00:08:15.779 --> 00:08:17.899
But I would submit to you in Genesis chapter two

00:08:17.899 --> 00:08:19.339
in verse number 15,

00:08:19.339 --> 00:08:23.119
that Adam was placed in the garden by God Almighty.

00:08:23.119 --> 00:08:26.179
And God said that he was put there to dress it

00:08:26.179 --> 00:08:27.420
and to keep it.

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:31.859
And the word dress it literally means to labor or to work.

00:08:31.859 --> 00:08:34.380
That's what the word means, that's what that phrase means.

00:08:34.380 --> 00:08:37.539
And so there are times in which we misunderstand the truth.

00:08:37.539 --> 00:08:42.020
Yes, work got a whole lot more complicated after the fall

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:45.460
with regard to the curse

00:08:45.460 --> 00:08:47.739
and the thorns and thistles and all of that.

00:08:47.739 --> 00:08:50.059
But the reality is that we find

00:08:50.059 --> 00:08:51.940
that God placed Adam in the garden

00:08:51.940 --> 00:08:53.820
according to Genesis 2.15,

00:08:53.820 --> 00:08:56.299
to dress it and to keep it.

00:08:56.299 --> 00:08:57.659
Who was he doing it for?

00:08:57.659 --> 00:08:59.239
He was doing it for God.

00:08:59.239 --> 00:09:00.080
He was doing it for God.

00:09:00.080 --> 00:09:03.859
God gave him, Adam, that responsibility.

